1
00:00:46,120 --> 00:00:48,400
I know you're fast with a gun,

2
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:52,040
but I'm not slow with a knife either.

3
00:00:53,200 --> 00:00:55,120
Why don't you put the gun down,

4
00:00:55,760 --> 00:00:57,440
and we can have a good talk.

5
00:01:14,320 --> 00:01:15,560
How did you find us?

6
00:01:16,120 --> 00:01:17,360
If I'm not mistaken,

7
00:01:18,320 --> 00:01:20,720
you're supposed to take the 3:00 p.m.

8
00:01:21,440 --> 00:01:23,570
international train to Europe today.

9
00:01:24,360 --> 00:01:26,480
But before getting on the train,

10
00:01:26,480 --> 00:01:29,039
you would definitely find a hiding place

11
00:01:29,039 --> 00:01:30,900
that is both safe and convenient.

12
00:01:32,720 --> 00:01:33,780
Look at this place.

13
00:01:34,520 --> 00:01:35,400
First,

14
00:01:35,560 --> 00:01:37,690
it's quite close to the train station,

15
00:01:37,720 --> 00:01:39,120
so you can board quickly.

16
00:01:39,440 --> 00:01:40,280
Second,

17
00:01:40,280 --> 00:01:41,560
it's away from the crowd.

18
00:01:41,560 --> 00:01:42,840
Too many people around

19
00:01:43,240 --> 00:01:45,400
would easily expose your whereabouts.

20
00:01:45,400 --> 00:01:46,200
Third,

21
00:01:47,080 --> 00:01:48,880
the transportation is convenient.

22
00:01:48,880 --> 00:01:50,479
If you encounter any danger,

23
00:01:50,920 --> 00:01:52,250
you can escape quickly.

24
00:01:53,479 --> 00:01:55,280
After considering all options,

25
00:01:55,320 --> 00:01:56,320
this is the place.

26
00:01:58,360 --> 00:01:59,920
Isn't she your target?

27
00:02:00,280 --> 00:02:02,610
Now that you have her, why don't you leave?

28
00:02:04,400 --> 00:02:05,480
I told you,

29
00:02:06,280 --> 00:02:08,280
my education was very traditional,

30
00:02:08,560 --> 00:02:10,160
and I'm very old-fashioned.

31
00:02:11,400 --> 00:02:12,520
So,

32
00:02:16,720 --> 00:02:18,079
since you gave me this,

33
00:02:19,600 --> 00:02:21,160
I have to return the favor.

34
00:02:22,160 --> 00:02:24,160
Otherwise, it's against the rules.

35
00:02:25,600 --> 00:02:26,280
Fine.

36
00:02:26,480 --> 00:02:27,480
What do you want?

37
00:02:29,360 --> 00:02:30,760
I can't bully you either.

38
00:02:32,440 --> 00:02:33,300
How about this?

39
00:02:34,440 --> 00:02:36,500
Let's have a gentleman's agreement.

40
00:02:36,920 --> 00:02:38,450
Neither of us uses weapons.

41
00:02:39,160 --> 00:02:40,280
Whoever loses

42
00:02:41,200 --> 00:02:42,600
is at the other's mercy.

43
00:02:45,440 --> 00:02:46,880
With the current situation,

44
00:02:46,880 --> 00:02:48,810
I don't have any other choice, do I?

45
00:02:49,720 --> 00:02:50,520
Come on.

46
00:04:31,560 --> 00:04:32,690
He has already lost.

47
00:04:32,760 --> 00:04:34,720
As promised, he will let us go.

48
00:04:35,080 --> 00:04:36,080
I don't trust him.

49
00:04:36,600 --> 00:04:38,040
I think he can be trusted.

50
00:04:39,000 --> 00:04:40,460
Even if he doesn't stop us,

51
00:04:40,600 --> 00:04:42,330
he can still notify the others.

52
00:04:42,360 --> 00:04:44,220
We still won't be able to get away.

53
00:04:44,560 --> 00:04:45,480
You are right.

54
00:04:46,280 --> 00:04:47,740
I am entrusted by someone,

55
00:04:48,360 --> 00:04:49,760
so I must fulfill my duty.

56
00:04:50,360 --> 00:04:52,159
I still have to follow the rules.

57
00:04:52,440 --> 00:04:53,840
I have to notify them.

58
00:04:54,400 --> 00:04:56,400
But I can wait until you get in the car

59
00:04:56,880 --> 00:04:58,080
before calling them.

60
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:11,800
Wait a minute.

61
00:05:15,720 --> 00:05:17,250
If you leave just like this,

62
00:05:18,520 --> 00:05:21,050
how am I supposed to explain it when I get back?

63
00:05:28,760 --> 00:05:29,560
Bro,

64
00:05:30,160 --> 00:05:31,360
put this on my tab too.

65
00:05:31,840 --> 00:05:32,970
That's two bullets.

66
00:05:34,200 --> 00:05:36,330
I'll pay you back when I get the chance.

67
00:06:05,600 --> 00:06:06,160
Alright,

68
00:06:06,360 --> 00:06:07,490
just see me off here.

69
00:06:07,640 --> 00:06:08,170
Bye-bye.

70
00:06:09,080 --> 00:06:11,410
Are your parting words really that short?

71
00:06:11,560 --> 00:06:13,640
Besides, I don't want you to say bye-bye.

72
00:06:13,640 --> 00:06:14,900
Then what should I say?

73
00:06:15,600 --> 00:06:16,880
Can you say zaijian?

74
00:06:18,120 --> 00:06:19,120
Isn't it the same?

75
00:06:21,120 --> 00:06:23,120
Although I am not a Chinese citizen,

76
00:06:23,200 --> 00:06:24,920
I grew up in China,

77
00:06:24,920 --> 00:06:27,250
and I have some understanding of Chinese.

78
00:06:27,320 --> 00:06:30,160
Zaijian, whether literally or connotatively,

79
00:06:30,160 --> 00:06:31,880
represents an expectation for each other

80
00:06:31,880 --> 00:06:33,320
and meeting again.

81
00:06:34,040 --> 00:06:35,400
But bye-bye doesn't.

82
00:06:35,800 --> 00:06:37,000
Alright, cut the crap.

83
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:37,840
Just go.

84
00:06:48,120 --> 00:06:49,159
Do you know

85
00:06:49,159 --> 00:06:51,600
what the probability is of two people meeting?

86
00:06:51,600 --> 00:06:52,400
No.

87
00:06:53,720 --> 00:06:55,200
It's 0.00487.

88
00:06:56,040 --> 00:06:57,040
Aren't you a computer guy?

89
00:06:57,040 --> 00:06:58,900
Why are you playing with math now?

90
00:06:59,040 --> 00:07:00,360
I mean,

91
00:07:01,640 --> 00:07:04,700
it's not easy to meet someone in this vast sea of people.

92
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:06,280
So I cherish it,

93
00:07:06,880 --> 00:07:08,160
because it's rare.

94
00:07:08,440 --> 00:07:11,640
I'm afraid I'll never see you again after turning around.

95
00:07:12,680 --> 00:07:13,560
So,

96
00:07:14,160 --> 00:07:15,620
do you think parting words

97
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:17,660
should be bye-bye or zaijian?

98
00:07:18,760 --> 00:07:21,160
Although we only spent a few days together,

99
00:07:22,040 --> 00:07:23,600
it was not very pleasant.

100
00:07:24,800 --> 00:07:26,530
You brought me so much trouble.

101
00:07:26,960 --> 00:07:28,720
If it weren't for someone's request,

102
00:07:28,720 --> 00:07:30,980
I would definitely not talk to you again.

103
00:07:31,160 --> 00:07:32,600
So let's not meet again.

104
00:07:33,640 --> 00:07:34,440
Bye.

105
00:08:50,520 --> 00:08:51,280
Hello.

106
00:08:52,320 --> 00:08:53,480
We have a situation.

107
00:08:54,560 --> 00:08:55,720
They ran away.

108
00:09:40,360 --> 00:09:43,640
Dad, I'm doing fine now.

109
00:09:44,400 --> 00:09:47,600
They made this place exactly like my room.

110
00:09:48,040 --> 00:09:50,600
I feel like I'm still at home.

111
00:09:51,960 --> 00:09:53,890
It feels like you're just outside.

112
00:09:54,880 --> 00:09:56,640
You don't need to worry about me.

113
00:09:56,640 --> 00:09:58,040
I am doing fine now.

114
00:09:58,560 --> 00:10:01,200
I've realized a lot of things lately.

115
00:10:02,240 --> 00:10:04,360
If I can get back safely,

116
00:10:04,800 --> 00:10:06,720
we must start our lives anew,

117
00:10:07,440 --> 00:10:08,080
okay?

118
00:10:34,400 --> 00:10:36,600
Did everything go well?

119
00:10:37,120 --> 00:10:38,120
It went smoothly.

120
00:10:50,120 --> 00:10:50,920
Where is she?

121
00:10:51,080 --> 00:10:51,880
She went out.

122
00:10:52,160 --> 00:10:53,360
Get some rest first.

123
00:10:53,360 --> 00:10:54,490
She'll be back soon.

124
00:11:27,000 --> 00:11:27,730
Sister Ning.

125
00:11:28,080 --> 00:11:29,960
When we see the young master later,

126
00:11:29,960 --> 00:11:31,760
you must put in a good word for me.

127
00:11:32,960 --> 00:11:34,520
Don't call me Sister Ning.

128
00:11:34,520 --> 00:11:36,040
I'm actually younger than you.

129
00:11:36,040 --> 00:11:37,770
Doesn't that make me sound old?

130
00:11:43,160 --> 00:11:44,890
Brother Tian is busy right now.

131
00:11:45,320 --> 00:11:46,440
Just wait a moment.

132
00:12:15,800 --> 00:12:17,000
Brother Long is here.

133
00:12:17,640 --> 00:12:19,570
Don't make fun of me, young master.

134
00:12:19,840 --> 00:12:20,640
Tell me,

135
00:12:21,000 --> 00:12:21,840
what is it?

136
00:12:22,640 --> 00:12:23,770
There was a problem.

137
00:12:24,720 --> 00:12:26,680
The woman still managed to...

138
00:12:26,680 --> 00:12:27,880
Did I tell you to stop?

139
00:12:42,040 --> 00:12:42,600
Brother Long.

140
00:12:42,600 --> 00:12:43,360
Continue.

141
00:12:44,720 --> 00:12:44,920
Shan...

142
00:12:44,920 --> 00:12:46,050
There was a problem.

143
00:12:46,600 --> 00:12:48,600
The woman still managed to get away.

144
00:13:00,360 --> 00:13:01,280
Mr. An,

145
00:13:02,960 --> 00:13:03,960
what do you think?

146
00:13:05,760 --> 00:13:07,020
We still have the item.

147
00:13:07,280 --> 00:13:08,840
As long as she doesn't come back,

148
00:13:08,840 --> 00:13:10,200
she's no threat to us.

149
00:13:14,640 --> 00:13:15,440
Brother Long.

150
00:13:15,880 --> 00:13:18,840
I personally have no problem with you,

151
00:13:20,080 --> 00:13:22,080
but with so many brothers under me,

152
00:13:23,920 --> 00:13:25,960
if everyone acted like you,

153
00:13:28,240 --> 00:13:30,120
I wouldn't be able to justify it.

154
00:13:32,520 --> 00:13:33,320
By the way,

155
00:13:33,760 --> 00:13:35,420
how is your arm from last time?

156
00:13:36,240 --> 00:13:37,040
I understand.

157
00:13:38,040 --> 00:13:39,040
Last time...

158
00:13:39,640 --> 00:13:41,040
My right arm just healed.

159
00:13:41,720 --> 00:13:42,450
This time...

160
00:13:43,360 --> 00:13:44,760
Can we switch to this one?

161
00:14:07,480 --> 00:14:09,440
Shh.

162
00:14:10,360 --> 00:14:11,690
I'm listening to music.

163
00:14:14,800 --> 00:14:15,600
Niu,

164
00:14:16,600 --> 00:14:18,060
take Long to the hospital.

165
00:14:35,960 --> 00:14:37,760
Lawyer An.

166
00:14:40,960 --> 00:14:43,420
I heard someone is messing with me recently.

167
00:14:45,160 --> 00:14:46,200
I'll handle it.

168
00:14:50,760 --> 00:14:51,560
Lawyer An,

169
00:14:53,200 --> 00:14:55,930
you've been taking good care of your skin lately.

170
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:05,460
What cosmetics do you use?

171
00:15:10,160 --> 00:15:11,160
Nothing special.

172
00:15:11,360 --> 00:15:13,920
I can recommend them if you need.

173
00:15:14,400 --> 00:15:15,640
I don't need it.

174
00:15:18,080 --> 00:15:19,200
You know me.

175
00:15:19,960 --> 00:15:22,120
If there are any good supplements,

176
00:15:23,240 --> 00:15:24,900
you can bring them to me later.

177
00:15:30,920 --> 00:15:32,380
I'm going to take a shower.

178
00:15:32,960 --> 00:15:35,080
Go handle the matter upstairs for me.

179
00:16:28,400 --> 00:16:29,400
Let's talk.
